title: Wrong data set result returned when an invalid filter expression 'row[0]' is set
description: When setting a filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0', the data set returns incorrect results or it returns a null result set.
OB: The data set returns incorrect results or a null result set when an invalid filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' is set.
EB: A relevant error message should pop up when an invalid filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' is set.
SR:
To reproduce this issue:
1. Set an invalid filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0'
2. Observe the incorrect results or null result set from the data set
